1
00:00:01,080 --> 00:00:02,900
Why are you so good to me?

2
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:04,433
I feel like I'm just a burden.

3
00:00:04,433 --> 00:00:06,425
I've never been able
to do anything nice for you.

4
00:00:06,425 --> 00:00:10,109
You're slowly improving in your own way.

5
00:00:10,109 --> 00:00:13,753
If one day Solar isn't around, we're doomed.

6
00:00:13,753 --> 00:00:15,992
Solar. Are you okay?

7
00:00:15,992 --> 00:00:18,813
I... am... Sun!

8
00:00:18,813 --> 00:00:21,280
Hey! Why are you doing this?

9
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:23,030
I get tired too, you know!

10
00:00:23,030 --> 00:00:24,811
I want to see my mom.

11
00:00:24,811 --> 00:00:26,261
Have you seen my boyfriend?

12
00:00:26,261 --> 00:00:27,827
Pobmek.

13
00:00:27,827 --> 00:00:29,907
What's going on?

14
00:00:33,787 --> 00:00:35,118
What?

15
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:38,035
I was acting like a 7-year-old kid,

16
00:00:38,035 --> 00:00:39,720
and said my name was Sun?

17
00:00:39,720 --> 00:00:43,043
Well, yeah.
The room was a complete mess yesterday.

18
00:00:43,043 --> 00:00:46,104
I had to clean up by myself all night.

19
00:00:49,052 --> 00:00:54,326
Don't tell me
you don't remember anything from yesterday.

20
00:00:55,563 --> 00:00:58,912
What I remember is...

21
00:00:59,740 --> 00:01:02,607
I heard a really loud car horn.

22
00:01:04,941 --> 00:01:09,739
After that, I don't remember anything.

23
00:01:12,901 --> 00:01:15,012
This morning I woke up here,

24
00:01:15,012 --> 00:01:18,345
took a shower, and went to the market.

25
00:01:23,026 --> 00:01:25,300
Hey! Where are you going?

26
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:28,543
What? I'm going to teach.

27
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:33,382
Solar, you just hit your head
on the ground yesterday.

28
00:01:33,382 --> 00:01:36,824
Then you woke up this morning
and couldn't remember anything.

29
00:01:36,824 --> 00:01:40,545
Don't go to work today.
Stay here and rest.

30
00:01:40,545 --> 00:01:42,220
It's too last-minute.

31
00:01:42,220 --> 00:01:43,916
I didn't apply for leave in advance.

32
00:01:43,916 --> 00:01:47,139
What about the kids in my class?
Who would take care of them?

33
00:01:50,027 --> 00:01:51,651
Are you joking?

34
00:01:52,409 --> 00:01:54,218
No, I'm not.

35
00:01:54,218 --> 00:01:56,160
I'm a teacher too.

36
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:58,923
I may not be their homeroom teacher
like you,

37
00:01:58,923 --> 00:02:01,430
but I can take care of the kids just fine.

38
00:02:04,662 --> 00:02:06,293
Hey.

39
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:09,650
Stay here and rest.

40
00:02:09,650 --> 00:02:13,444
I'll talk to Sodchuen for you, okay?

41
00:02:16,190 --> 00:02:18,762
- Is that okay?
- Fine.

42
00:02:18,762 --> 00:02:21,506
Go take a shower. You're already late.

43
00:02:24,308 --> 00:02:26,623
You're the cutest.

44
00:03:52,639 --> 00:03:54,869
One, two, three!

45
00:03:57,501 --> 00:03:58,818
Roar!

46
00:03:58,818 --> 00:04:00,672
- Come on, good job!
- Good job!

47
00:04:00,672 --> 00:04:03,450
Now go to class.

48
00:04:03,450 --> 00:04:04,829
Hey, Teacher Pobmek.

49
00:04:04,829 --> 00:04:06,430
I didn't see you earlier this morning.

50
00:04:06,430 --> 00:04:08,739
You must've slept well.

51
00:04:09,396 --> 00:04:12,021
I made it in time to teach, didn't I?

52
00:04:12,021 --> 00:04:13,179
Morning, Sodchuen.

53
00:04:13,179 --> 00:04:14,524
Morning.

54
00:04:14,524 --> 00:04:17,165
Didn't Solar come with you?

55
00:04:17,165 --> 00:04:18,814
Is he still not feeling better?

56
00:04:18,814 --> 00:04:20,186
He's better.

57
00:04:20,186 --> 00:04:21,975
He was being stubborn
and insisted on coming to teach,

58
00:04:21,975 --> 00:04:24,003
but I asked him to take the day off.

59
00:04:24,003 --> 00:04:27,000
I think I'm going to cover Grade 2, Class 1
for him today.

60
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,238
Are you sure?

61
00:04:28,238 --> 00:04:31,690
Solar's students are quite stubborn.

62
00:04:33,057 --> 00:04:36,328
I think the stubborn one is him.

63
00:04:39,836 --> 00:04:41,636
Solar!

64
00:04:51,118 --> 00:04:53,795
Solar really wouldn't give up teaching.

65
00:04:53,795 --> 00:04:57,602
Teacher Solar is really responsible.

66
00:04:57,602 --> 00:05:00,329
He's perfect for you, Teacher Pobmek.

67
00:05:02,835 --> 00:05:04,120
Alright.

68
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,626
It's time to teach.

69
00:05:05,626 --> 00:05:08,681
Let's go do the work we love.

70
00:05:08,681 --> 00:05:11,722
Teacher Jee, don't forget
what I asked you to do.

71
00:05:11,722 --> 00:05:12,861
Yes, ma'am.

72
00:05:12,861 --> 00:05:15,118
Bye. See you.

73
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:25,760
[Teacher Maprang: OK, Teacher Don: OK,
Teacher Solar: Seems fine]

74
00:05:27,789 --> 00:05:29,723
Hey, hold on.

75
00:05:32,235 --> 00:05:35,134
- What are you writing down?
- This?

76
00:05:35,134 --> 00:05:37,125
It's the student safeguarding log.

77
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:38,431
What's that?

78
00:05:38,431 --> 00:05:43,296
A teacher at the main campus
has been acting off.

79
00:05:43,296 --> 00:05:44,975
On the outside, everything seemed normal,

80
00:05:44,975 --> 00:05:49,328
but one day,
the teacher suddenly had mood swings,

81
00:05:49,328 --> 00:05:52,626
and was later diagnosed
with a mental condition.

82
00:05:54,142 --> 00:05:57,210
I think Sodchuen's worried
our teachers might end up like that.

83
00:05:58,856 --> 00:06:02,437
And how is that teacher now?

84
00:06:02,437 --> 00:06:05,627
He hasn't been teaching for a while.

85
00:06:07,096 --> 00:06:09,229
It's been taken care of, I heard.

86
00:06:13,953 --> 00:06:16,633
But why did Sodchuen assign you to this?

87
00:06:17,290 --> 00:06:20,528
She probably just wanted to see how I'd do.

88
00:06:20,528 --> 00:06:23,732
She keeps praising me, saying I'm amazing.

89
00:06:24,404 --> 00:06:26,998
She just says things like that, doesn't she?

90
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:37,533
Jee is amazing, isn't he?

91
00:06:37,533 --> 00:06:41,247
He represented the university
in an academic competition abroad

92
00:06:41,247 --> 00:06:43,785
and even came back with a scholarship.

93
00:06:43,785 --> 00:06:46,650
You should reach out to him sometime, Pobmek.

94
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:49,323
Do you want me to ask for his number
so you two can reconnect?

95
00:06:49,323 --> 00:06:51,544
No, Mom.

96
00:06:51,544 --> 00:06:53,989
Jee has his own circle of friends.

97
00:06:53,989 --> 00:06:55,807
And I have mine here.

98
00:06:55,807 --> 00:06:59,059
By the way, who's your roommate?

99
00:06:59,059 --> 00:07:00,799
What's he studying?

100
00:07:00,799 --> 00:07:02,095
He's studying to become a teacher.

101
00:07:02,095 --> 00:07:05,527
I feel like anyone can become a teacher
these days.

102
00:07:05,527 --> 00:07:09,040
I even see some teachers looking things up
on the internet

103
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:11,800
just to teach their students.

104
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,207
If you could spend time
with people studying medicine or accounting...

105
00:07:14,207 --> 00:07:16,133
Mom, I have to go.

106
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,870
Solar.

107
00:07:29,870 --> 00:07:31,261
I...

108
00:07:32,258 --> 00:07:34,113
I apologize on behalf of my mom for...

109
00:07:34,113 --> 00:07:35,913
Damn!

110
00:07:40,894 --> 00:07:42,846
I got straight As.

111
00:07:43,813 --> 00:07:46,103
I'm top of the class.

112
00:07:46,103 --> 00:07:48,989
Damn. Congrats.

113
00:07:48,989 --> 00:07:51,219
How are your grades?

114
00:08:04,017 --> 00:08:05,823
Is something wrong?

115
00:08:08,662 --> 00:08:10,208
No.

116
00:08:12,601 --> 00:08:16,247
You just won't admit it, huh?

117
00:08:18,316 --> 00:08:20,620
Come on. Let me show you something.

118
00:08:30,297 --> 00:08:35,441
In child psychology, there's a concept called
an idiosyncratic mand.

119
00:08:36,428 --> 00:08:39,023
It's a unique word or phrase a child uses

120
00:08:39,023 --> 00:08:42,130
to communicate when they need help.

121
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:44,899
For example,

122
00:08:44,899 --> 00:08:49,131
some children may have been taught
to be afraid of asking for help.

123
00:08:49,131 --> 00:08:51,320
They might think

124
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:53,200
they have to solve every problem
on their own,

125
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,469
so they keep everything to themselves.

126
00:08:57,085 --> 00:09:01,630
So we teach them to use another word instead,

127
00:09:01,630 --> 00:09:04,559
so they don't have to worry
about saying it out loud.

128
00:09:04,559 --> 00:09:06,659
What word?

129
00:09:06,659 --> 00:09:08,336
It can be anything.

130
00:09:08,336 --> 00:09:11,393
For example, this kid doesn't like the rain.

131
00:09:11,393 --> 00:09:14,507
When he needs help, what does he say?

132
00:09:14,507 --> 00:09:16,430
Raincoat?

133
00:09:17,857 --> 00:09:19,265
Yes.

134
00:09:20,036 --> 00:09:25,440
As soon as he says that,
his friends know he needs help.

135
00:09:27,007 --> 00:09:33,429
Wait, why are you telling me this?
I'm not a kid.

136
00:09:37,056 --> 00:09:38,641
Are you sure?

137
00:09:44,565 --> 00:09:48,336
Silent, huh? No answer?

138
00:09:49,059 --> 00:09:52,823
Alright. Just let me know when you're ready.

139
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:13,145
Has anyone learned this before?
Does anyone know?

140
00:10:13,145 --> 00:10:14,936
- Me.
- Okay.

141
00:10:14,936 --> 00:10:17,586
Alright, I'll tell you the first one.
What are these pink things?

142
00:10:17,586 --> 00:10:20,443
- Flowers.
- Flowers? Okay, write "flowers".

143
00:10:20,443 --> 00:10:22,778
What do they look like?
Go ahead and draw them.

144
00:10:22,778 --> 00:10:24,578
Yeah.

145
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:32,360
[Boyfriend]

146
00:10:36,747 --> 00:10:38,745
So you're napping here.

147
00:10:59,521 --> 00:11:01,726
Wake up, Teacher.

148
00:11:10,259 --> 00:11:12,339
Uncle Kidnapper.

149
00:11:17,258 --> 00:11:18,889
Sun?

150
00:11:34,697 --> 00:11:36,325
What is this place?

151
00:11:36,325 --> 00:11:39,762
It's... the school.

152
00:11:39,762 --> 00:11:41,141
So Mom is going to pick me up, right?

153
00:11:41,141 --> 00:11:42,941
Yay!

154
00:11:43,624 --> 00:11:44,965
No, no, no.

155
00:11:44,965 --> 00:11:49,632
Little Sun, let's go home with Uncle.

156
00:11:49,632 --> 00:11:51,795
- Mom's home, right?
- Our home.

157
00:11:52,585 --> 00:11:54,248
No! I'm not going!

158
00:11:54,248 --> 00:11:56,113
I'm going to see Mom!

159
00:11:56,868 --> 00:11:58,827
Sun, come back here!

160
00:12:03,017 --> 00:12:04,930
Where did he go?

161
00:12:09,924 --> 00:12:11,230
Oh!

162
00:12:12,279 --> 00:12:14,079
Hello.

163
00:12:18,136 --> 00:12:20,010
There you are!

164
00:12:22,352 --> 00:12:24,152
No!

165
00:12:28,203 --> 00:12:30,984
Teacher Solar, could you check my vocab?

166
00:12:30,984 --> 00:12:33,662
Teacher Solar, could you check my homework?

167
00:12:33,662 --> 00:12:35,361
Teacher Solar, could you check my answers?

168
00:12:35,361 --> 00:12:37,509
Hey! I said my name's not Solar!

169
00:12:37,509 --> 00:12:40,509
My name is Sun! It's Sun, got it?

170
00:12:43,635 --> 00:12:45,850
- It hurts!
- Then stay still!

171
00:12:45,850 --> 00:12:48,059
Stay still?

172
00:12:48,059 --> 00:12:49,859
Ouch!

173
00:12:57,098 --> 00:13:00,798
Make it fierce and powerful!
One, two, three!

174
00:13:08,322 --> 00:13:10,844
Go ahead and stretch. I'll be right back.

175
00:13:14,631 --> 00:13:16,174
Hey, Pobmek.

176
00:13:21,170 --> 00:13:22,806
What's going on, Elsa?

177
00:13:22,806 --> 00:13:24,987
Yeah, what's going on?

178
00:13:24,987 --> 00:13:28,731
The Teacher Pobmek-Teacher Jee ship
is sailing!

179
00:13:29,581 --> 00:13:30,921
What are you looking for?

180
00:13:30,921 --> 00:13:34,177
Nothing. I just came to get some air.

181
00:13:34,177 --> 00:13:36,469
"I'm worried about you."

182
00:13:36,469 --> 00:13:39,406
"Solar isn't treating you right, is he?"

183
00:13:39,406 --> 00:13:41,303
Don't you have a class to teach?

184
00:13:41,303 --> 00:13:42,763
Why are you out here getting some air?

185
00:13:42,763 --> 00:13:44,821
You're not teaching during class time either.

186
00:13:44,821 --> 00:13:50,117
"Don't make me lose control
and kiss you right now."

187
00:13:51,084 --> 00:13:52,811
Are you sick?

188
00:13:56,551 --> 00:13:57,970
You feel a little warm.

189
00:13:57,970 --> 00:13:59,738
What are you doing?

190
00:13:59,738 --> 00:14:01,538
I'm fine.

191
00:14:24,094 --> 00:14:25,639
What are you guys doing?

192
00:14:25,639 --> 00:14:30,136
Teacher Solar! I swear I didn't skip P.E.

193
00:14:31,656 --> 00:14:33,057
You looked so cool just now!

194
00:14:33,057 --> 00:14:34,264
Huh?

195
00:14:34,264 --> 00:14:35,372
I'm Sun.

196
00:14:35,372 --> 00:14:36,913
What are your names?

197
00:14:37,561 --> 00:14:40,554
I'm Four. He's King.

198
00:14:42,013 --> 00:14:44,614
Oh, I need your help.

199
00:14:44,614 --> 00:14:46,408
I need to get out of here.

200
00:14:46,408 --> 00:14:47,888
Do you know any secret ways out?

201
00:14:47,888 --> 00:14:50,490
Please. Don't try to trick us, Teacher Solar.

202
00:14:50,490 --> 00:14:53,110
You're going to send us to
Principal Sodchuen, aren't you?

203
00:14:53,110 --> 00:14:57,157
Hey, I'm not tricking you guys.
My name's really Sun, not Solar.

204
00:14:57,157 --> 00:15:00,898
If you're really not Teacher Solar,
then show us the secret code.

205
00:15:00,898 --> 00:15:03,112
Gen Y wouldn't know how to do it.

206
00:15:05,968 --> 00:15:10,120
Damn. That's so sigma!

207
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:12,402
Hey! Teacher Pobmek is coming!

208
00:15:13,377 --> 00:15:16,669
Guys, I have to go!
Please tell me the way.

209
00:15:16,669 --> 00:15:19,052
Behind the gym, there's a wall
you can jump over to get out.

210
00:15:19,052 --> 00:15:20,398
Hurry there, Sun.

211
00:15:20,398 --> 00:15:22,024
Cool.

212
00:15:30,492 --> 00:15:33,324
Hey, have you guys seen Teacher Solar?

213
00:15:35,948 --> 00:15:37,657
Are you going to tell me or not?

214
00:15:39,082 --> 00:15:42,797
If not, I'll give you
a huge set of math problems.

215
00:15:42,797 --> 00:15:44,540
Are you going to tell me or not?

216
00:15:49,708 --> 00:15:52,555
Hey, Teacher Solar.

217
00:15:52,555 --> 00:15:54,360
You're not teaching?

218
00:15:55,955 --> 00:15:57,914
I saw Teacher Pobmek earlier.

219
00:15:57,914 --> 00:16:02,739
He seemed a little off. He felt kind of warm.
I think he's unwell.

220
00:16:06,807 --> 00:16:11,238
But now you seem even more off than him.

221
00:16:17,725 --> 00:16:18,923
Hey!

222
00:16:18,923 --> 00:16:20,670
Uncle Kidnapper, let go!

223
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:22,396
Uncle Kidnapper?

224
00:16:22,396 --> 00:16:23,718
What's that?

225
00:16:23,718 --> 00:16:24,779
Is something going on?

226
00:16:24,779 --> 00:16:25,982
I said no!

227
00:16:25,982 --> 00:16:27,166
Let go!

228
00:16:27,166 --> 00:16:30,544
Something's definitely going on.
Teacher Solar is squirming like crazy.

229
00:16:32,052 --> 00:16:34,134
The kids are watching.

230
00:16:38,283 --> 00:16:40,247
Just tell me what's going on.

231
00:16:46,252 --> 00:16:47,684
Hey! Pobmek!

232
00:16:47,684 --> 00:16:49,827
I don't use pencils! I only use pens!

233
00:16:49,827 --> 00:16:51,352
Hey!

234
00:16:52,570 --> 00:16:54,728
Write whatever you want.

235
00:16:54,728 --> 00:16:57,246
No one is as good as you, Jee!

236
00:16:59,115 --> 00:17:00,421
Let's go!

237
00:17:00,421 --> 00:17:02,021
Hey!

238
00:17:07,766 --> 00:17:09,863
Aren't you tired?

239
00:17:09,863 --> 00:17:12,438
You've been running away from Uncle all day.

240
00:17:13,604 --> 00:17:16,520
I told you. I just want to see Mom.

241
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:19,981
And I already told you
I'd take you to see her.

242
00:17:19,981 --> 00:17:22,729
Can't you wait until school is over?

243
00:17:25,183 --> 00:17:28,461
Luckily, Solar is free all day today.

244
00:17:28,461 --> 00:17:30,480
This afternoon he only has to teach...

245
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:32,400
[Teacher Solar's Schedule]

246
00:17:32,665 --> 00:17:34,518
What should I do?

247
00:17:35,406 --> 00:17:38,940
Can a kidnapper be a teacher too?

248
00:17:41,044 --> 00:17:43,885
I said I'm not a kidnapper.

249
00:17:43,885 --> 00:17:46,282
You sure look like one.

250
00:17:46,282 --> 00:17:48,614
What kind of teacher
has no kids who like him?

251
00:17:48,614 --> 00:17:49,807
Even I'm better than you.

252
00:17:49,807 --> 00:17:52,338
I've only been here a little while,
but I've already made two friends.

253
00:17:52,338 --> 00:17:53,505
Sure.

254
00:17:53,505 --> 00:17:56,038
You're the best.

255
00:18:08,742 --> 00:18:13,319
But there's one thing you can't beat me at.

256
00:18:13,319 --> 00:18:14,854
What?

257
00:18:14,854 --> 00:18:16,487
Teaching.

258
00:18:16,487 --> 00:18:18,232
You're a kid.

259
00:18:18,232 --> 00:18:23,384
Even if I were a kidnapper,
I'd still be better at teaching than you.

260
00:18:24,502 --> 00:18:26,162
Please!

261
00:18:26,162 --> 00:18:31,835
I'm sure I can teach better than you, Uncle.

262
00:18:47,317 --> 00:18:51,520
Anyone who gets out of their seat
will be in big trouble.

263
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:57,840
[Do all the questions on Page 36]

264
00:18:57,840 --> 00:18:59,760
[Class 2/1]
Alright, kids.

265
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:02,800
Today, Teacher Solar is going to...

266
00:19:09,220 --> 00:19:10,713
This word is pronounced "sun".

267
00:19:10,713 --> 00:19:12,811
Who knows what it means in Thai?

268
00:19:12,811 --> 00:19:14,489
Sun means "Phra Arthit".

269
00:19:14,489 --> 00:19:15,616
Very good.

270
00:19:15,616 --> 00:19:18,158
It's also my name.

271
00:19:18,158 --> 00:19:20,923
- Huh? How come?
- His name is Solar.

272
00:19:20,923 --> 00:19:26,316
Well, Teacher Solar just wants
to use the name Sun for a day.

273
00:19:26,316 --> 00:19:29,893
Excuse me, can I change my name to Anna?

274
00:19:29,893 --> 00:19:31,465
Then can I change my name to Jaii?

275
00:19:31,465 --> 00:19:34,102
No! My name is really Sun!

276
00:19:34,102 --> 00:19:39,173
So your name is "Really Sun", not just "Sun"?

277
00:19:39,173 --> 00:19:40,973
Teachers!

278
00:19:56,281 --> 00:19:59,948
Hey, no one beats kids with sticks anymore.

279
00:20:04,606 --> 00:20:09,075
Okay, let's learn how to count
from 1 to 10 in English.

280
00:20:09,075 --> 00:20:12,402
But we learned that in first grade already.

281
00:20:16,165 --> 00:20:19,347
Here. "Head" means "Hua",
and "neck" means "Kor".

282
00:20:19,347 --> 00:20:20,916
And...

283
00:20:20,916 --> 00:20:22,497
Teacher!

284
00:20:22,497 --> 00:20:25,630
What's the difference
between neck and throat?

285
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:29,046
(Kor.)

286
00:20:30,505 --> 00:20:32,588
What do you think?

287
00:20:33,775 --> 00:20:36,305
"Neck" probably means
the outside part of the neck,

288
00:20:36,305 --> 00:20:39,402
because you wear a necklace
around your neck.

289
00:20:39,402 --> 00:20:42,460
And "throat" probably means the inside,

290
00:20:42,460 --> 00:20:45,526
like when you say, "My throat hurts".

291
00:20:51,123 --> 00:20:53,533
Beautiful and smart. Ten out of ten!

292
00:21:09,954 --> 00:21:12,116
Can I play too?

293
00:21:12,116 --> 00:21:15,575
Hey! You guys are loud over there!
Teacher Sun is teaching.

294
00:21:15,575 --> 00:21:17,361
- Be quiet!
- That's right!

295
00:21:17,361 --> 00:21:19,977
How can you be playing in my class?

296
00:21:19,977 --> 00:21:22,535
Oh, race cars.

297
00:21:31,597 --> 00:21:34,338
Keep playing in my class
and those hands are done!

298
00:21:34,338 --> 00:21:36,520
Where's the class leader?
Write their names down.

299
00:21:36,520 --> 00:21:38,198
Come on, Teacher Solar.

300
00:21:38,198 --> 00:21:39,351
Don't you remember my name?

301
00:21:39,351 --> 00:21:41,914
I said I'm Sun.

302
00:21:41,914 --> 00:21:43,593
- Write your own name down too.
- Huh?

303
00:21:43,593 --> 00:21:45,993
So, can I change my name to Anna?

304
00:21:45,993 --> 00:21:47,303
Write her name down too.

305
00:21:47,303 --> 00:21:50,672
What? How come
you can change your name, but I can't?

306
00:21:50,672 --> 00:21:55,739
I want to change my name from Tinker Bell
to Tinky Winky too.

307
00:22:11,375 --> 00:22:12,972
Hey!

308
00:22:14,789 --> 00:22:17,541
I told you not to get out of your seats!

309
00:22:17,541 --> 00:22:20,520
I didn't get out of my seat, Teacher.

310
00:22:20,520 --> 00:22:25,162
I'll send you all to Principal Sodchuen
for not listening to me.

311
00:22:25,162 --> 00:22:28,145
We've all finished copying the answers.

312
00:22:28,145 --> 00:22:31,144
Look. Did I do well?

313
00:22:38,453 --> 00:22:39,578
You got this!

314
00:22:39,578 --> 00:22:41,418
You got this!

315
00:22:58,918 --> 00:23:00,314
Teacher Solar!

316
00:23:00,314 --> 00:23:02,231
What are you doing?

317
00:23:04,225 --> 00:23:06,322
Hey! Students!

318
00:23:07,569 --> 00:23:11,238
Who made the room such a mess, huh?

319
00:23:15,137 --> 00:23:16,991
Teacher Solar?

320
00:23:18,046 --> 00:23:20,130
What happened?

321
00:23:21,815 --> 00:23:24,863
I've said it hundreds of times.
My name is Sun!

322
00:23:24,863 --> 00:23:27,013
It's Sun!

323
00:23:39,539 --> 00:23:43,427
Teacher Pobmek, this is serious.

324
00:23:44,233 --> 00:23:46,624
Why is Solar acting like that?

325
00:23:46,624 --> 00:23:49,244
Why is he referring to himself as Sun?

326
00:23:49,244 --> 00:23:50,669
Yeah.

327
00:23:50,669 --> 00:23:54,907
He's acting strange, almost like a child.

328
00:23:57,934 --> 00:24:00,123
There's nothing wrong with Solar.

329
00:24:00,821 --> 00:24:01,950
He's perfectly fine.

330
00:24:01,950 --> 00:24:05,729
Perfectly fine? How?

331
00:24:05,729 --> 00:24:08,929
That's way out of character for him.

332
00:24:16,572 --> 00:24:17,972
Wait...

333
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:21,949
Are you okay?

334
00:24:21,949 --> 00:24:23,809
Are you not feeling well?

335
00:24:28,808 --> 00:24:29,949
Here.

336
00:24:29,949 --> 00:24:31,749
Put this on.

337
00:24:45,579 --> 00:24:48,120
Teacher Jee, what should we do?

338
00:24:54,993 --> 00:24:57,590
Jee! Don't write a report about Solar!

339
00:24:57,590 --> 00:25:00,623
Then don't keep everything to yourself!

340
00:25:02,164 --> 00:25:06,533
You said you're fine, but you're clearly not.

341
00:25:08,225 --> 00:25:11,025
It's not going to solve anything.

342
00:25:18,927 --> 00:25:20,976
Jee is amazing, isn't he?

343
00:25:20,976 --> 00:25:24,667
He represented the university
in an academic competition abroad,

344
00:25:24,667 --> 00:25:27,607
and even came back with a scholarship.

345
00:25:27,607 --> 00:25:29,332
Jee is amazing, isn't he?

346
00:25:29,332 --> 00:25:31,720
[If Jee is so amazing,
why not make him your own kid, Mom?]

347
00:26:18,265 --> 00:26:19,857
Are you okay?

348
00:26:22,146 --> 00:26:23,599
I'm fine.

349
00:26:24,807 --> 00:26:26,770
Nothing's wrong with me.

350
00:26:34,695 --> 00:26:39,733
I know you like to solve problems
on your own,

351
00:26:40,793 --> 00:26:44,652
but the more you do this, the worse I feel.

352
00:26:46,764 --> 00:26:49,244
You act like I can't help you at all.

353
00:27:06,656 --> 00:27:08,330
I'm sorry.

354
00:27:13,465 --> 00:27:16,131
If you don't want to say it directly,

355
00:27:16,131 --> 00:27:18,139
why don't you try using a magic word?

356
00:27:32,816 --> 00:27:34,464
Sponge bath.

357
00:27:35,189 --> 00:27:36,988
I'm giving you a sponge bath, aren't I?

358
00:27:39,059 --> 00:27:40,859
No.

359
00:27:41,644 --> 00:27:46,046
I mean, my magic word is "sponge bath".

360
00:27:55,411 --> 00:27:57,835
If there's ever a day
I can't take it anymore,

361
00:27:59,551 --> 00:28:01,819
can you give me a sponge bath?

362
00:28:04,398 --> 00:28:05,820
Of course.

363
00:28:06,676 --> 00:28:08,473
If there's ever a day
you can't take it anymore,

364
00:28:08,473 --> 00:28:10,545
I'll give you a sponge bath.

365
00:28:23,231 --> 00:28:25,031
Sponge bath.

366
00:28:29,619 --> 00:28:31,433
What did you say?

367
00:28:32,319 --> 00:28:34,823
I mean...

368
00:28:36,953 --> 00:28:38,732
can you help me?

369
00:28:52,457 --> 00:28:54,536
Well...

370
00:28:54,536 --> 00:28:57,636
Solar's mind reverts to that of a 7-year-old.

371
00:28:58,733 --> 00:29:03,528
I think it's the effect
from his accident the other day.

372
00:29:08,477 --> 00:29:11,099
But he seemed fine this morning.

373
00:29:11,099 --> 00:29:12,475
Yeah.

374
00:29:12,475 --> 00:29:14,616
But somehow, this afternoon,

375
00:29:14,616 --> 00:29:18,280
he suddenly went back to being a kid,
as you can see.

376
00:29:19,860 --> 00:29:25,036
I didn't want anyone to see Solar like this.

377
00:29:29,506 --> 00:29:34,213
But it can't be helped. It was an accident.

378
00:29:35,063 --> 00:29:37,443
You didn't have to hide it from us.

379
00:29:40,668 --> 00:29:43,840
I was just afraid Jee would report it.

380
00:29:46,629 --> 00:29:51,692
You know
how much Solar loves being a teacher.

381
00:29:54,450 --> 00:29:58,600
I was afraid that if the school found out,
then...

382
00:29:58,600 --> 00:30:00,603
Jee! I told you not to write it down!

383
00:30:00,603 --> 00:30:02,653
Teacher Jee, write it big.

384
00:30:02,653 --> 00:30:06,167
Teacher Solar is the one
we need to support the most.

385
00:30:06,167 --> 00:30:07,449
Huh?

386
00:30:09,246 --> 00:30:11,096
What do you mean?

387
00:30:11,096 --> 00:30:16,517
We're going to help Solar, of course.

388
00:30:18,206 --> 00:30:21,968
Yes, just like how we helped
the teacher at the main campus.

389
00:30:23,446 --> 00:30:24,969
Hold on.

390
00:30:24,969 --> 00:30:27,311
Didn't that teacher get fired?

391
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:30,039
I thought you said that teacher was gone.

392
00:30:30,039 --> 00:30:34,344
I meant the teacher has been taken care of,
as in recovered.

393
00:30:35,493 --> 00:30:40,115
The school is aware
and concerned about all the teachers,

394
00:30:40,115 --> 00:30:44,340
so I asked Teacher Jee
to help keep an eye on our teachers.

395
00:30:44,340 --> 00:30:48,843
In case something happens,
we can support them in time.

396
00:30:53,041 --> 00:30:55,624
Let us help, Pobmek.

397
00:30:56,818 --> 00:30:59,521
Solar is my junior too.

398
00:31:02,494 --> 00:31:03,714
But how are you?

399
00:31:03,714 --> 00:31:07,324
Will you be alright?
You don't really get along well with kids.

400
00:31:10,219 --> 00:31:11,575
On the bright side,

401
00:31:11,575 --> 00:31:15,534
it's a good coincidence
that Sun is 7 years old.

402
00:31:15,534 --> 00:31:17,796
This should be easy.

403
00:31:17,796 --> 00:31:19,115
Easy?

404
00:31:19,115 --> 00:31:20,257
Easy how?

405
00:31:20,257 --> 00:31:24,623
No one's better at dealing with
7-year-olds than we are!

406
00:31:25,842 --> 00:31:27,396
You're right.

407
00:31:27,396 --> 00:31:29,923
Come on. We can do it!

408
00:31:36,332 --> 00:31:39,099
The reason I've gathered everyone here today

409
00:31:39,099 --> 00:31:40,855
is to inform you of something.

410
00:31:40,855 --> 00:31:44,615
The person sitting here
is not the Teacher Solar we know.

411
00:31:44,615 --> 00:31:46,772
Now, he's Little Sun.

412
00:31:46,772 --> 00:31:50,303
- Please take good care of him, everyone.
- Hello...

413
00:31:52,352 --> 00:31:54,432
Little Sun, right?

414
00:31:58,357 --> 00:31:59,382
Okay, Aunt.

415
00:31:59,382 --> 00:32:01,182
Sure.

416
00:32:02,272 --> 00:32:05,718
Sun, someone wants to talk to you.

417
00:32:11,665 --> 00:32:15,943
Sun, Uncle Pobmek is a good person.

418
00:32:15,943 --> 00:32:18,308
He can be trusted.

419
00:32:18,308 --> 00:32:22,733
If you behave, Mom will hurry to pick you up.

420
00:32:24,744 --> 00:32:26,544
Alright.

421
00:32:28,708 --> 00:32:32,920
Kids, remember what I taught you
about getting into animal characters?

422
00:32:32,920 --> 00:32:37,054
Our teacher Solar has to take on
the character of Little Sun on some days.

423
00:32:37,054 --> 00:32:40,320
You're all his friends,
so please be kind to Little Sun.

424
00:32:40,320 --> 00:32:43,903
- Okay?
- Okay!

425
00:32:59,775 --> 00:33:03,431
It's kind of surreal, isn't it?

426
00:33:04,383 --> 00:33:07,534
The whole thing
about Solar turning into a kid.

427
00:33:07,534 --> 00:33:12,990
But at least when he's Sun,
he's pretty easy to handle.

428
00:33:12,990 --> 00:33:15,397
He's way sweeter than some kids.

429
00:33:15,397 --> 00:33:17,427
How?

430
00:33:18,214 --> 00:33:20,838
He's probably the most chaotic in the school.

431
00:33:22,872 --> 00:33:26,736
I think you're wrong, Pobmek.

432
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:41,520
[I'm sorry I was so bad
I made you sick, Uncle]

433
00:33:43,718 --> 00:33:47,447
At least Sun stopped calling you Kidnapper.

434
00:34:09,474 --> 00:34:10,921
Jee.

435
00:34:13,693 --> 00:34:18,246
I said a lot of bad things to you today.

436
00:34:20,189 --> 00:34:22,104
- Actually, I...
- Hey, no worries!

437
00:34:22,104 --> 00:34:24,011
I don't like you.

438
00:34:24,011 --> 00:34:26,134
Huh? What do you mean?

439
00:34:28,418 --> 00:34:32,322
I mean, I used to not like you.

440
00:34:36,826 --> 00:34:39,526
You're just perfect at everything.

441
00:34:40,683 --> 00:34:44,760
And my mom kept praising you so much
all the time

442
00:34:44,760 --> 00:34:46,375
that it annoyed me,

443
00:34:48,622 --> 00:34:52,232
even though you did nothing wrong.

444
00:35:02,311 --> 00:35:04,111
Perfect?

445
00:35:05,961 --> 00:35:08,243
You know what?

446
00:35:08,243 --> 00:35:14,677
I have to see a psychotherapist for my OCD.

447
00:35:18,334 --> 00:35:20,613
I'm not perfect like you think.

448
00:35:25,486 --> 00:35:27,286
But I...

449
00:35:29,260 --> 00:35:32,593
I really want to be your friend, Pobmek.

450
00:35:37,374 --> 00:35:38,932
Okay.

451
00:35:39,710 --> 00:35:42,180
You already are.

452
00:35:42,180 --> 00:35:44,136
You've been for a long time.

453
00:35:50,521 --> 00:35:56,736
In the future,
you and that Jee guy might become friends.

454
00:36:16,248 --> 00:36:21,230
Are you ready, Mr. Pobmek,
for this week's sponge bath?

455
00:36:25,276 --> 00:36:27,918
My final exam score still sucks as always!

456
00:36:27,918 --> 00:36:29,833
My mom won't stop praising that freaking Jee!

457
00:36:29,833 --> 00:36:31,105
Damn it!

458
00:36:31,105 --> 00:36:34,268
Who cares if he's top of the class?
I'm not him!

459
00:36:34,268 --> 00:36:36,891
And I never wanted to study accounting
in the first place!

460
00:36:36,891 --> 00:36:40,091
That's why my score sucks like this!

461
00:36:45,533 --> 00:36:48,050
That's enough. That's enough.

462
00:36:51,101 --> 00:36:53,021
You did great.

463
00:36:53,756 --> 00:36:57,694
When you can't take it anymore,
you should let it out.

464
00:36:57,694 --> 00:37:01,864
You might feel stressed or not okay now,

465
00:37:01,864 --> 00:37:05,527
but I believe time will help you.

466
00:37:08,609 --> 00:37:10,400
Who knows?

467
00:37:10,400 --> 00:37:15,614
In the future,
you and that Jee guy might become friends.

468
00:37:15,614 --> 00:37:17,346
No way!

469
00:37:17,346 --> 00:37:19,624
I don't want to be friends with him!

470
00:37:31,582 --> 00:37:35,526
Are you going to keep holding my hand
until tomorrow morning?

471
00:37:49,554 --> 00:37:51,628
Hey, guys.

472
00:37:51,628 --> 00:37:55,587
We know how to deal with Sun now,

473
00:37:55,587 --> 00:38:01,932
but I wonder if Solar will come back.

474
00:38:10,644 --> 00:38:12,625
I don't know either.

475
00:38:19,225 --> 00:38:21,982
Alright, forget it.

476
00:38:21,982 --> 00:38:24,960
Let's split up and head home.

477
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:28,837
Things might be better tomorrow.

478
00:38:28,837 --> 00:38:30,371
I guess.

479
00:38:31,048 --> 00:38:32,180
Come on.

480
00:38:32,180 --> 00:38:34,580
Let's go home, guys.

481
00:38:37,441 --> 00:38:40,751
Oh, but who's going
to wake him up, Teacher Jee?

482
00:38:49,106 --> 00:38:50,592
Guys.

483
00:38:51,423 --> 00:38:57,441
I think I have an idea
when the two will switch.

484
00:39:20,793 --> 00:39:24,593
You startled me! Why are you up so early?

485
00:39:24,593 --> 00:39:27,734
Are you Solar?

486
00:39:27,734 --> 00:39:29,115
Of course I am.

487
00:39:29,115 --> 00:39:30,927
Who else could I be?

488
00:39:32,627 --> 00:39:33,696
I figured it out!

489
00:39:33,696 --> 00:39:36,412
You switch between being yourself and Sun
every time you wake up.

490
00:39:36,412 --> 00:39:37,674
Huh?

491
00:39:37,674 --> 00:39:39,934
Am I still switching to a kid?

492
00:39:41,448 --> 00:39:42,801
Yes.

493
00:39:42,801 --> 00:39:48,446
Yesterday, you fell asleep during the day,
and woke up as Sun.

494
00:39:51,967 --> 00:39:53,720
But don't worry.

495
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:56,149
I'm going to help you get better
no matter what.

496
00:40:05,502 --> 00:40:07,418
So...

497
00:40:08,798 --> 00:40:11,589
does this mean you'll always have
to take care of me like this?

498
00:40:21,835 --> 00:40:23,744
Are you forcing yourself?

499
00:40:25,351 --> 00:40:27,241
Don't force yourself.

500
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:29,680
If it gets too much,
you need to take a break.

501
00:40:29,680 --> 00:40:31,135
Got it?

502
00:40:32,194 --> 00:40:34,933
Yeah. I know.

503
00:40:42,353 --> 00:40:44,044
Solar, that's enough.

504
00:40:44,044 --> 00:40:47,848
What do you mean, enough?
You're too cute! I can't help it!

505
00:40:47,848 --> 00:40:51,339
You usually just do things on your own.

506
00:40:53,952 --> 00:40:57,315
Solar, that's enough. Come on, be shy!

507
00:41:01,886 --> 00:41:03,072
It's fine.

508
00:41:03,072 --> 00:41:04,916
We're all grown-ups here.

509
00:41:06,920 --> 00:41:09,477
Teacher Solar just kissed you six times.

510
00:41:09,477 --> 00:41:10,865
I was counting.

511
00:41:10,865 --> 00:41:13,221
So please kiss him back that many times.

512
00:41:13,221 --> 00:41:15,621
My OCD is asking.

513
00:41:22,116 --> 00:41:23,916
Sponge bath?

514
00:41:25,307 --> 00:41:26,903
Yeah.

515
00:41:33,606 --> 00:41:34,608
You're the best!

516
00:41:34,608 --> 00:41:36,670
You let others help you now, right?

517
00:41:36,670 --> 00:41:37,803
Yeah.

518
00:41:37,803 --> 00:41:39,330
Oh, come here!

519
00:41:39,330 --> 00:41:41,099
Solar! That's enough! Be shy!

520
00:41:41,099 --> 00:41:44,842
- Even though it seemed tough at first,
- Come here!

521
00:41:44,842 --> 00:41:47,779
Because it was a challenge
I'd never faced before,

522
00:41:47,779 --> 00:41:51,327
- That's enough!
- and I chose to carry it all by myself,

523
00:41:52,817 --> 00:41:56,322
but now that I've finally gathered the courage
to ask for help,

524
00:41:58,299 --> 00:42:00,965
everything feels a lot lighter.

525
00:42:00,965 --> 00:42:07,643
It makes me realize
I'm not going through this alone anymore.

526
00:42:37,225 --> 00:42:39,590
If you don't get back to your old self soon,

527
00:42:39,590 --> 00:42:41,813
our room's going to
turn into a toy graveyard.

528
